SimbaSC progressed to the Azam Sports Federation Cup (ASFC) final after beating Azam FC 1-0 at Majimaji Stadium in Songea, Ruvuma this evening. The Dar es Salaam based club were forced to wait until 89th minute of the game for Louis Micquisson to convert a free kick to change the scoreboard. Simba will face their traditional rivals Young Africans in Kigoma in the final game of the tourney. Young Africans sailed through to the ASFC final after eliminating Biashara United at Ali Hassan Mwinyi Stadium in Tabora on Friday.